---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="System Integration | Intelio - Connect Your Systems" description="Connect fragmented business systems so information flows automatically instead of being manually copied between platforms.">
<main class="bg-white">
  <!-- SECTION 1: HERO -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[90vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden bg-black">
    <!-- Video Background -->
    <video 
      autoplay
      muted
      loop
      playsinline
      preload="auto"
      webkit-playsinline="true"
      x5-playsinline="true"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
      style="min-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; width: auto; height: auto;"
    >
      <source src="/videos/system-integration-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4">
      Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>
    
    <!-- Dark Overlay for Text Readability -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/55 z-[1]"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-24 w-full">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <!-- Label -->
        <div class="mb-6">
          <span class="text-blue-400 text-sm font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase">
            SYSTEM INTEGRATION
          </span>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Headline -->
        <h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-7xl text-white leading-[1.1] mb-6 tracking-tight">
          Systems Stay in Sync Automatically
        </h1>
        
        <!-- Subhead -->
        <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-gray-200 mb-10 leading-relaxed">
          Data entered once. Propagates everywhere. No re-entry. No manual coordination. No bottleneck.
        </p>
        
        <!-- CTA Button -->
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white text-lg font-semibold rounded-xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-2xl transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
          Start a Project
          <svg class="ml-2 w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 2: INTRO -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl text-gray-900 mb-8">
        Connect Your Systems. Remove Manual Work.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Most businesses run on disconnected systems. Data lives in silos. Someone is responsible for keeping everything in sync—manually copying information between platforms, re-entering data, and coordinating workflows.
        </p>
        <p>
          Intelio builds system integrations that make data flow automatically. Information entered once propagates everywhere. No re-entry. No manual coordination. No bottleneck.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-600">
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
          This isn't consulting. This isn't advice. It's infrastructure.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 3: WHAT'S BROKEN & WHAT CHANGES (SIDE BY SIDE) -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 relative">
        <!-- Vertical Divider Line -->
        <div class="hidden md:block absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-px bg-black transform -translate-x-1/2"></div>
        
        <!-- Left Column: What's Broken Today -->
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="mb-12">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-blue-600 mb-4 block">WHAT'S BROKEN TODAY</span>
          </div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Manual Data Replication</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Customer data entered in CRM, re-entered in accounting, re-entered in project management. Same person. Multiple systems. Hours per week wasted.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Disconnected Workflows</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Deal closes in CRM but finance doesn't know. Project completes but accounting doesn't see it. Information moves in silos, not synchronized.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">System Conflicts</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Different systems show different customer data. Finance sees one version, operations sees another. Decisions made on conflicting information.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 4 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">No Single Source of Truth</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Customer address lives in three places. Which one is right? Nobody knows. Financial reconciliation becomes guesswork.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right Column: What Changes After Deployment -->
        <div>
          <div class="mb-12">
            <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-blue-600 mb-4 block">WHAT CHANGES AFTER DEPLOYMENT</span>
          </div>
          
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Automatic Information Flow</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Data entered once, propagates everywhere automatically. No re-entry. No manual copying. No human bottleneck.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Real-Time Synchronization</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Deal closes at 4 PM. Invoice exists in accounting by 4:15 PM. One source of truth, updated as events happen.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Built-In Conflict Detection</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                System detects when data diverges across systems and alerts you before decisions get made on bad information.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 4 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Time Freed for Revenue Work</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                The person whose job was syncing systems? That 10-15 hours per week is now available for core business work.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 5 -->
            <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200 ease-out">
              <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Complete Audit Trail</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
                Every data movement recorded. Who updated what. When it changed. Why it moved. Compliance and debugging become straightforward.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 5: HOW IT WORKS -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-16">
        <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-blue-600 mb-4 block">HOW THE SYSTEM ACTUALLY WORKS</span>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Card 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Input Layer</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Your data already exists in systems you operate (CRM, accounting, project management). The integration continuously monitors for changes: new records created, existing records modified, status transitions, financial transactions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Decision Logic</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            The system applies rules you define. Where should this data go? How should it be formatted for the target system? If data exists in multiple places, which version is authoritative? What conditions require human review?
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Action Layer</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Based on the logic, the system executes automatically. Creates or updates records in target systems. Sends notifications when data moves. Triggers downstream workflows. Generates audit logs with complete records of what moved, when, and why.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 4 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4">Oversight Layer</h3>
          <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Humans stay in control. The system routes exceptions to people when needed. Requires approval for sensitive operations if configured. Provides dashboards showing what moved, what failed, what needs attention. Can be paused immediately. Can be reconfigured as business rules change.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 6: ENGAGEMENT MODELS -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-16">
        <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-blue-600 mb-4 block">ENGAGEMENT MODELS</span>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Card 1: Build + Maintain -->
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Build + Maintain</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">You own operations. We monitor and optimize.</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">You Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Day-to-day decisions about data flows and business rules</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">We Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">System monitoring, performance tuning, infrastructure health</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Best For</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Operations or IT teams that can own the workflow. You want monthly support, not daily involvement.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Pricing</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Project fee + monthly maintenance</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2: Build + Operate -->
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">Build + Operate</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">We embed and manage the system end-to-end.</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">You Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Overall business outcomes and strategy</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">We Own</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Daily operations, monitoring, optimization, exception handling, business rule updates</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Best For</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">You want integrations to "just work" without your team managing them. You need someone accountable for data accuracy end-to-end.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Pricing</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Monthly operating retainer</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 7: OUR PROCESS -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-16">
        <span class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.08em] text-blue-600 mb-4 block">OUR PROCESS</span>
      </div>
      
      <div class="space-y-12">
        <!-- Step 01 -->
        <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold">
            01
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-3">System Audit</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              We map your current data landscape. What systems do you use? What data lives where? What's currently manual? Where are the biggest pain points?
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 italic">
              You get: Clear documentation of current state and specific integration opportunities with ROI estimates
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 02 -->
        <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold">
            02
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-3">Workflow Specification</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              You define how data should flow. What are the rules for each integration? What exceptions need human review? What data transformations are needed?
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 italic">
              You get: Detailed integration specification that becomes the build plan
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 03 -->
        <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold">
            03
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-3">Build & Test</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              We build integrations and validate with your real data. Real data testing, not synthetic. Validation against your rules. Exception handling tested. Performance verified.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 italic">
              You get: Working integrations, tested and ready to deploy
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 04 -->
        <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold">
            04
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-3">Pilot Deployment</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              Run integrations on a limited basis. One data flow live. Monitor accuracy and performance. Gather feedback. Refine before full deployment.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 italic">
              You get: Confidence that the system works before going live
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 05 -->
        <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold">
            05
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-2xl text-gray-900 mb-3">Full Deployment & Handoff</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              Deploy to full operation. All integrations live. Team training. Monitoring dashboards set up. Support plan defined.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 italic">
              You get: Live system, monitored and supported according to your engagement model
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 8: WHAT YOU GET & WHO THIS IS FOR -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-16">
        <!-- Left Column: What You Get -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12">
            What You Get
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-6">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
              </svg>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Automatic Data Flow</h3>
